## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-294">Quando um <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> escreve o texto para seu fluxo padrão, que o texto geralmente é exibido no console.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-294">When a <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes text to its standard stream, that text is typically displayed on the console.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-295">Definindo <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A> para `true` para redirecionar o <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo, você pode manipular ou suprimir a saída de um processo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-295">By setting <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A> to `true` to redirect the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, you can manipulate or suppress the output of a process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-296">Por exemplo, o texto de filtro, formatá-los de maneira diferente ou escrever a saída para o console e um arquivo de log designado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-296">For example, you can filter the text, format it differently, or write the output to both the console and a designated log file.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="072a1-297">Você deve definir <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A> para `false` se você deseja definir <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A> para `true`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-297">You must set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A> to `false` if you want to set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A> to `true`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-298">Caso contrário, ler o <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo lança uma exceção.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-298">Otherwise, reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream throws an exception.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-299">O redirecionamento <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo pode ser lido de forma síncrona ou assíncrona.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-299">The redirected <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream can be read synchronously or asynchronously.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-300">Métodos como <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>, e <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> executar operações de leitura síncronas no fluxo de saída do processo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-300">Methods such as <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>, and <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> perform synchronous read operations on the output stream of the process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-301">Esses síncrona ler operações não concluída até associado <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> grava seu <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo ou fecha o fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-301">These synchronous read operations do not complete until the associated <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes to its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, or closes the stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-302">Por outro lado, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> inicia assíncrona operações de leitura no <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-302">In contrast, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> starts asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-303">Esse método permite que um manipulador de eventos designado (consulte <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.OutputDataReceived>) para a saída de fluxo e imediatamente retorna ao chamador, que pode executar outras tarefas enquanto a saída de fluxo é direcionada para o manipulador de eventos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-303">This method enables a designated event handler (see <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.OutputDataReceived>) for the stream output and immediately returns to the caller, which can perform other work while the stream output is directed to the event handler.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="072a1-304">O aplicativo que está processando a saída assíncrona deve chamar o <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> método para garantir que o buffer de saída foi liberado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-304">The application that is processing the asynchronous output should call the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> method to ensure that the output buffer has been flushed.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-305">Síncrona ler operações apresentam uma dependência entre o chamador leem o <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo e o filho processam gravação nesse fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-305">Synchronous read operations introduce a dependency between the caller reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream and the child process writing to that stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-306">Essas dependências podem causar condições de deadlock.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-306">These dependencies can cause deadlock conditions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-307">Quando o chamador lê o fluxo redirecionado de um processo filho, é dependente de filho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-307">When the caller reads from the redirected stream of a child process, it is dependent on the child.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-308">O chamador espera para a operação de leitura até que o filho grava no fluxo ou fecha o fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-308">The caller waits for the read operation until the child writes to the stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-309">Quando o processo filho grava dados suficientes para preencher seu fluxo redirecionado, ele é dependente de pai.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-309">When the child process writes enough data to fill its redirected stream, it is dependent on the parent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-310">O processo filho aguarda a próxima operação de gravação até que o pai lê o fluxo total ou fecha o fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-310">The child process waits for the next write operation until the parent reads from the full stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-311">A condição de deadlock ocorre quando o chamador e o processo filho aguardam uns aos outros para concluir uma operação, e não pode continuar.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-311">The deadlock condition results when the caller and child process wait for each other to complete an operation, and neither can continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-312">Você pode evitar deadlocks avaliando as dependências entre o chamador e o processo filho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-312">You can avoid deadlocks by evaluating dependencies between the caller and child process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-313">Por exemplo, o código c# a seguir mostra como ler de um fluxo redirecionado e aguarde até que a saída do processo filho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-313">For example, the following C# code shows how to read from a redirected stream and wait for the child process to exit.</span></span>  
  
```  
Process p = new Process();  
p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;  
p.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true;  
p.StartInfo.FileName = "Write500Lines.exe";  
p.Start();  
  
// To avoid deadlocks, always read the output stream first and then wait.  
string output = p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-314">O exemplo de código evita uma condição de deadlock chamando `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` antes de `p.WaitForExit`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-314">The code example avoids a deadlock condition by calling `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` before `p.WaitForExit`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-315">Uma condição de deadlock pode surgir se o pai processar chamadas `p.WaitForExit` antes de `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` e o processo filho grava texto suficiente para preencher o fluxo redirecionado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-315">A deadlock condition can result if the parent process calls `p.WaitForExit` before `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill the redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-316">O processo pai deve esperar indefinidamente para o saída do processo filho.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-316">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to exit.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-317">O processo filho seria espere indefinidamente pai leiam completa <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-317">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-318">Há um problema semelhante ao ler todo o texto de fluxos de erro padrão e a saída padrão.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-318">There is a similar issue when you read all text from both the standard output and standard error streams.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-319">Por exemplo, o código c# a seguir executa uma operação de leitura em ambos os fluxos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-319">For example, the following C# code performs a read operation on both streams.</span></span>  
  
```  
// To avoid deadlocks, use asynchronous read operations on at least one of the streams.  
// Do not perform a synchronous read to the end of both redirected streams.  
p.BeginOutputReadLine();  
string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-320">O exemplo de código evita a condição de deadlock pela execução assíncrona de operações de leitura de <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-320">The code example avoids the deadlock condition by performing asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-321">Resultados de uma condição de deadlock se o pai processar chamadas `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` seguido `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` e o processo filho grava texto suficiente para preencher seu fluxo de erro.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-321">A deadlock condition results if the parent process calls `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` followed by `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill its error stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-322">O processo pai deve esperar indefinidamente para o processo filho fechar seu <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-322">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to close its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-323">O processo filho seria espere indefinidamente pai leiam completa <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> fluxo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-323">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="072a1-324">Você pode usar operações de leitura assíncronas para evitar essas dependências e seu possíveis de deadlock.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-324">You can use asynchronous read operations to avoid these dependencies and their deadlock potential.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="072a1-325">Como alternativa, você pode evitar a condição de deadlock criando dois threads e lendo a saída de cada fluxo em um thread separado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="072a1-325">Alternately, you can avoid the deadlock condition by creating two threads and reading the output of each stream on a separate thread.</span></span>  
  
   
  
